{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:33:46.625Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"je4dsp1f","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/backend/README.md","result":"  1 | # GFF AI Local MVP Backend Foundation\n  2 | \n  3 | Welcome to the local FastAPI MVP backend foundation for the GFF AI Enterprise platform. This module provides local developer API capabilities, SQLite storage connectivity, system health monitoring, and a fully configured local CORS workspace to interface seamlessly with the Next.js frontend.\n  4 | \n  5 | ---\n  6 | \n  7 | ## Architecture Overview\n  8 | \n  9 | The backend uses a standard, modular clean-architecture layout built for Python 3.12+ and FastAPI:\n 10 | \n 11 | ```text\n 12 | backend/\n 13 | ├── app/\n 14 | │   ├── __init__.py\n 15 | │   ├── api.py           # Core endpoints (Health, SystemLogs)\n 16 | │   ├── config.py        # Settings & Pydantic Config Validation\n 17 | │   ├── database.py      # SQLAlchemy DB Connection & Dependency Injection\n 18 | │   ├── main.py          # FastAPI App Entrypoint & CORS Middleware\n 19 | │   ├── models.py        # SQLAlchemy Declarative Models\n 20 | │   └── schemas.py       # Pydantic Schemas (V2)\n 21 | ├── .env.example         # Template for environment configuration\n 22 | ├── .gitignore           # Local development ignores\n 23 | ├── README.md            # Execution manual\n 24 | └── requirements.txt     # Python Dependencies\n 25 | ```\n 26 | \n 27 | ## Features\n 28 | \n 29 | - **Automated DB Bootstrap**: Automatically boots a local SQLite database (`dev.db`) on application launch.\n 30 | - **Enterprise Logs**: A simple, high-performance database logger schema for auditing backend/frontend handshakes.\n 31 | - **Health Verification**: An endpoint at `/api/v1/health` that dynamically validates database status and platform health.\n 32 | - **Next.js Alignment**: Built-in CORS and request timing telemetry middleware matching frontend-dev requirements.\n 33 | - **Clean Interactive Specs**: Automatic redirect of root `/` path to the interactive OpenAPI UI (`/docs`).\n 34 | \n 35 | ---\n 36 | \n 37 | ## Local Setup & Run Guide\n 38 | \n 39 | ### 1. Prerequisites\n 40 | Ensure you have **Python 3.12+** and **pip** installed:\n 41 | ```bash\n 42 | python3 --version\n 43 | pip3 --version\n 44 | ```\n 45 | \n 46 | ### 2. Set Up Virtual Environment\n 47 | Move to the backend folder and create a clean Python virtual environment:\n 48 | ```bash\n 49 | cd backend\n 50 | python3 -m venv venv\n 51 | ```\n 52 | \n 53 | Activate the environment:\n 54 | - **macOS / Linux**:\n 55 |   ```bash\n 56 |   source venv/bin/activate\n 57 |   ```\n 58 | - **Windows**:\n 59 |   ```bash\n 60 |   venv\\Scripts\\activate\n 61 |   ```\n 62 | \n 63 | ### 3. Install Dependencies\n 64 | ```bash\n 65 | pip install -r requirements.txt\n 66 | ```\n 67 | \n 68 | ### 4. Set Up Environment Config\n 69 | Copy the example environment file:\n 70 | ```bash\n 71 | cp .env.example .env\n 72 | ```\n 73 | The defaults in `.env` are pre-tuned for seamless local development with the Next.js local frontend.\n 74 | \n 75 | > ⚠️ **Production Security Warning**:\n 76 | > In local development mode, `JWT_SECRET` defaults to a safe developer-only fallback key. However, for any production deployment, you **MUST** override `JWT_SECRET` in your environment variables with a cryptographically secure, high-entropy key (e.g., generated via `openssl rand -hex 32`). Leaving the default key active in production compromises token verification and authentication security.\n 77 | \n 78 | ### 5. Seed the Local Database\n 79 | Seed the SQLite database with representative GFF AI multi-tenant development data (including 4 client accounts, 4 projects, 4 agent operations, 4 documents, 4 invoices, 3 support tickets, and 3 governance compliance records) and pre-configured role-based development users:\n 80 | \n 81 | ```bash\n 82 | python app/seed.py\n 83 | ```\n 84 | \n 85 | #### Pre-Configured Developer Accounts & Roles:\n 86 | - **GFF Admin Lead** (Global Operations):\n 87 |   - Email: `gff_admin@gff.ai`\n 88 |   - Role: `gff_admin`\n 89 |   - Password: `password123`\n 90 | - **Apex Admin Lead** (Client Tenant Admin):\n 91 |   - Email: `client_admin@apex.com`\n 92 |   - Role: `client_admin`\n 93 |   - Tenant: Apex Global\n 94 |   - Password: `password123`\n 95 | - **Apex Analyst** (Client Tenant Member):\n 96 |   - Email: `client_member@apex.com`\n 97 |   - Role: `client_member`\n 98 |   - Tenant: Apex Global\n 99 |   - Password: `password123`\n100 | - **Legacy Fallback Admin**:\n101 |   - Email: `admin@gff.ai`\n102 |   - Role: `admin`\n103 |   - Password: `gff_enterprise_admin_pass_2026`\n104 | - **Legacy Fallback Client**:\n105 |   - Email: `client@chevron.com`\n106 |   - Role: `client`\n107 |   - Tenant: Chevron Corporation\n108 |   - Password: `chevron_secure_pass_2026`\n109 | \n110 | #### Idempotency & Database Resetting:\n111 | - Running `python app/seed.py` repeatedly is perfectly **idempotent**; it checks for existing records before inserting, ensuring no duplicated keys or rows.\n112 | - To safely **wipe all tables and fresh-seed** a clean slate, run with the `--reset` flag:\n113 |   ```bash\n114 |   python app/seed.py --reset\n115 |   ```\n116 | \n117 | ### 6. Run the Server\n118 | Launch the development server via Uvicorn:\n119 | ```bash\n120 | uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000\n121 | ```\n122 | \n123 | Once running, you can access:\n124 | - **Interactive OpenAPI Documentation**: [http://localhost:8000/docs](http://localhost:8000/docs)\n125 | - **Service Health Check Endpoint**: [http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health](http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health)\n126 | \n127 | ---\n128 | \n129 | ## API Documentation\n130 | \n131 | ### GET `/api/v1/health`\n132 | Checks backend and database health.\n133 | **Response (200 OK)**:\n134 | ```json\n135 | {\n136 |   \"status\": \"healthy\",\n137 |   \"timestamp\": 1719493200.0,\n138 |   \"database\": {\n139 |     \"status\": \"healthy\",\n140 |     \"error\": null\n141 |   },\n142 |   \"services\": {\n143 |     \"api\": \"healthy\",\n144 |     \"gff_core\": \"operational\"\n145 |   },\n146 |   \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n147 | }\n148 | ```\n149 | \n150 | ### GET `/api/v1/logs`\n151 | Returns the recent list of system log entries.\n152 | **Response (200 OK)**:\n153 | ```json\n154 | []\n155 | ```\n156 | \n157 | ### POST `/api/v1/logs`\n158 | Creates a test system log.\n159 | **Request Payload**:\n160 | ```json\n161 | {\n162 |   \"level\": \"INFO\",\n163 |   \"message\": \"Next.js frontend handshake completed successfully\",\n164 |   \"module\": \"handshake\"\n165 | }\n166 | ```\n167 | **Response (201 Created)**:\n168 | ```json\n169 | {\n170 |   \"id\": 1,\n171 |   \"level\": \"INFO\",\n172 |   \"message\": \"Next.js frontend handshake completed successfully\",\n173 |   \"module\": \"handshake\",\n174 |   \"created_at\": \"2026-06-27T15:10:00.000000\"\n175 | }\n176 | ```","success":true},{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/backend/.env.example","result":" 1 | # GFF AI - Local MVP Backend Environment Variables\n 2 | \n 3 | # App Environment Configuration\n 4 | ENVIRONMENT=development\n 5 | PROJECT_NAME=\"GFF AI Enterprise API\"\n 6 | API_V1_STR=/api/v1\n 7 | \n 8 | # Local SQLite Database Configuration\n 9 | DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./dev.db\n10 | \n11 | # Security Configuration (Local Development Placeholders - DO NOT USE IN PRODUCTION)\n12 | JWT_SECRET=gff_ai_super_secret_local_key_for_jwt_tokens_2026\n13 | ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=11520 # 8 days in minutes\n14 | \n15 | # CORS Policy - Allowed Origins (JSON array format or comma-separated string)\n16 | CORS_ORIGINS=[\"http://localhost:3000\",\"http://127.0.0.1:3000\"]","success":true}],"durationMs":3}}
